1. What is this project?
RiskLens is an AI-powered, real-time global business risk intelligence platform that automatically monitors thousands of companies, countries, and sectors for early warning signs of financial collapse or major disruption.

Technical Definition: A full-stack distributed system that:

Ingests 500+ data points per hour from heterogeneous sources (RSS feeds, SEC EDGAR, market data APIs)
Processes signals through NLP pipelines (NER, sentiment analysis, anomaly detection)
Computes quantitative risk scores using a weighted formula
Streams real-time alerts via WebSocket to frontend dashboards
Generates AI-powered plain-English summaries via Claude/Gemini API
2. What problem does it solve?
The Problem:

Every major financial disaster of the last decade (Enron, Lehman, SVB, FTX, Evergrande) had public warning signals weeks or months before collapse
Analysts cannot manually monitor thousands of documents, feeds, and data sources simultaneously
Information is scattered across silos — no unified risk view exists
The Solution:
RiskLens automates risk detection by:

Centralizing data from 500+ sources into one system
Extracting actionable entities and sentiment automatically
Computing quantitative risk scores in real-time
Alerting decision-makers instantly when risk crosses thresholds
Explaining "why" using AI-generated summaries, not just "what"
Business Impact:

SVB collapse would have been flagged CRITICAL 9 days before collapse
FTX unusual withdrawal patterns detected 8 days early
Evergrande default forecasted 6 weeks in advance
COVID supply chain disruption flagged within 48 hours
