7. Why were these technologies chosen instead of alternatives?
Backend: FastAPI vs Express.js vs Django vs Go

Express.js: Eliminated because Python ecosystem is superior for data science + ML
Django: Overkill, too much magic; FastAPI is lighter, faster, more modern
Go: Would require rewriting all ML integration libraries; Python is standard in ML
FastAPI Wins: Async by default, auto-docs, validation, modern Python
Database: PostgreSQL vs MongoDB vs DynamoDB

MongoDB: Schema flexibility is a liability for financial data; need ACID guarantees
DynamoDB: AWS vendor lock-in, expensive at scale, no transactions
PostgreSQL Wins: ACID compliance (critical for financial data), JSON columns (hybrid flexibility), async driver
Frontend: React vs Vue vs Svelte vs Angular

Vue: Smaller ecosystem for Three.js integration
Svelte: Smaller community, fewer component libraries for complex dashboards
Angular: Too verbose, steep learning curve, unnecessary for this project
React Wins: Largest ecosystem (Three.js, Chart.js, etc.), JSX readability, community size
AI: Claude vs GPT vs LLaMA vs Gemini

Claude 3.5 Sonnet: Best reasoning + instruction-following, good context window (200k)
GPT-4: More expensive, but would also work
LLaMA: Open-source but requires hosting, less reliable for financial analysis
Claude Wins: Best cost/performance ratio, no need to host own models
Vector DB: Qdrant vs Pinecone vs Weaviate vs Milvus

Pinecone: SaaS pricing adds cost, vendor lock-in
Weaviate: Heavier deployment footprint
Milvus: More complex to operate
Qdrant Wins: Self-hosted, lightweight, fast, great REST API
8. Explain the project's business logic.
Core Workflow:

Key Business Rules:

Score Computation Frequency: Every entity rescored every 15 minutes
Signal Window: Risk scores consider signals from last 7/30/90 days (configurable)
Alert Triggers: Only HIGH (60+) and CRITICAL (80+) create alerts
AI Summary: Only generated when score crosses threshold (saves Claude API quota)
Cache Strategy: Results cached for 5 minutes → balance freshness vs load
Role-Based Access: Viewers see all data; analysts can configure alerts
Watchlist: Users can follow specific entities for personalized alerts
