11. Explain the project in 3 minutes
"RiskLens is an AI-powered risk intelligence platform designed to predict financial collapses weeks before they happen. I built the entire system from scratch — backend, frontend, data pipeline, and deployment.

Problem Statement:
SVB, FTX, Evergrande, Lehman — every major financial disaster of the past decade had public warning signals weeks or months before collapse. But analysts can't humanly monitor thousands of documents across multiple sources simultaneously. Information is fragmented across silos — news feeds, SEC filings, market data, social signals. There's no unified risk view.

Architecture Overview:
The system is a three-tier distributed application:

TIER 1: Data Ingestion Pipeline

Celery background workers ingest data every 5-30 minutes
RSS feeds from Reuters, Bloomberg, BBC, FT, AP (news signals)
SEC EDGAR API for official filings (8-K, 10-K, 10-Q forms)
Alpha Vantage for real-time market data (stock prices, volumes)
Each data point is tagged with source, URL, publication date
TIER 2: NLP Processing Pipeline

spaCy for named entity recognition (extracts company names, countries, people)
HuggingFace transformers for sentiment analysis (-1 to +1 scores)
Keyword-based sector inference (Finance, Tech, Energy, Healthcare, etc.)
Vector embeddings stored in Qdrant for semantic search
All processing is async to handle concurrent batch operations
TIER 3: Risk Computation & Visualization

Risk scoring formula combines three factors:
Sentiment Delta (40% weight): Change in avg sentiment relative to baseline
Volume Anomaly (30% weight): Z-score of signal volume (unusual spike in coverage?)
Price Volatility (30% weight): Stock price % change vs threshold
Formula outputs normalized 0-100 score
Score classified into severity: LOW (0-35), MEDIUM (35-60), HIGH (60-80), CRITICAL (80+)
High-risk scores trigger Claude API calls for AI-generated summaries
Alerts published to Redis Pub/Sub → streamed to all connected frontend clients via WebSocket
Frontend Architecture:

React 18 with TypeScript for type safety
Zustand for lightweight state management
React Query for API data fetching + intelligent caching
Three.js for 3D Galaxy Map visualization (each star = entity, brightness = risk)
Chart.js for risk timeline and sector analysis
Framer Motion for smooth animations
Responsive design with Tailwind CSS
Real-time WebSocket listener that updates risk feed as alerts arrive
Key Features:

Galaxy Map: 3D interactive visualization where each tracked entity is a star. Star size and brightness indicate risk level. Color-coded by severity (cyan = low, amber = high, red = critical). Click any star to open entity detail panel.

Live Risk Feed: Real-time streaming of HIGH/CRITICAL alerts via WebSocket. Shows entity name, severity, current risk score, timestamp. Updated as alerts are triggered (not polling).

Natural Language Query Bar: Type questions like "What's the risk to our supply chain?" or "Which banks are in crisis?" Claude analyzes your question + context and returns answers. Uses hybrid search: semantic (vector DB) + keyword matching.

Risk Dashboard: Summary stats (total entities, alerts today, critical alerts). Bar chart of sector risk distribution. Spotlight on highest-risk entity.

Timeline Explorer: View risk score history for any entity over custom time windows (7, 30, 90, 180 days). Useful for post-mortems and trend analysis.

Entity Detail Panel: Complete history for any entity including all signals, risk scores, AI summaries from Claude, watchlist status.

PDF Reports: Generate audit-ready reports with charts and summaries using jsPDF.

Authentication & Security:

JWT tokens (HS256) with 60-minute expiry
bcrypt password hashing (not plain-text)
Role-based access: analyst (full access) vs viewer (read-only)
Rate limiting: 100 requests/minute per IP
CORS restrictions
ORM (SQLAlchemy) prevents SQL injection
React escaping prevents XSS
Environment variables for secrets (no hardcoded API keys)
Database Schema (PostgreSQL):

Users table: email, hashed_password, role, is_active
Entities table: name, type (company/country/sector/person), sector, ticker, country
Signals table: entity_id, source, signal_type, raw_text, sentiment_score, published_at
RiskScores table: entity_id, score, severity, sentiment_delta, volume_anomaly, price_volatility, computed_at
AISummaries table: entity_id, summary_text, severity, contributing_signals, recommended_action
Alerts table: entity_id, severity, message, triggered_at, acknowledged
Watchlists table: user_id, entity_id (join table)
Caching Strategy:

Redis cache with configurable TTLs (5 min for risk scores, 1 min for live alerts)
Cache keys: 'entities:list:{page}:{filter}', 'alerts:recent:{hours}', etc.
Cache invalidation on new score computation or alert
Pub/Sub for WebSocket broadcasting (no polling)
Demo Data: Seeded with 25+ historical entities and 500+ signals demonstrating predictive accuracy:

SVB Bank: Flagged CRITICAL 9 days before March 10, 2023 collapse
FTX Exchange: HIGH risk 8 days before November 8, 2022 bankruptcy
Evergrande: CRITICAL status 6 weeks before default in December 2021
COVID Supply Chain: Early detection of disruption patterns in January 2020
Russia-Ukraine: Energy crisis flagged within 48 hours of February 24, 2022 invasion
Technical Excellence:

Fully async codebase (FastAPI + asyncpg)
Proper error handling + structured logging (structlog)
Comprehensive test suite (pytest)
Docker containerization for reproducibility
Database migrations with Alembic (version control for schema)
Rate limiting with slowapi
