Comprehensive inline documentation
Potential Interview Questions & Answers:

"How would you scale this to monitor 1 million entities?" → Partition signals by entity hash, use read replicas, implement caching layer, move to distributed queue (Kafka vs Celery)
"What if Claude API goes down?" → Fallback summaries, cache results, implement circuit breaker pattern
"How do you detect anomalies?" → Z-score for volume, sentiment delta for mood shifts, price volatility for market moves
"Why not use a NoSQL database?" → Financial data needs ACID guarantees; PostgreSQL with JSON columns gives flexibility + safety
"How do you prevent false positives?" → Multi-factor scoring (sentiment + volume + price), configurable thresholds, manual oversight"
12. Technical Explanation (For Engineers)
System Design:

This is a Lambda Architecture hybrid combining:

Batch Processing: Celery workers run scheduled NLP/risk computation tasks
Stream Processing: WebSocket broadcasts alerts in real-time via Redis Pub/Sub
Key Architectural Decisions:

Async-First Design

FastAPI uses asyncio event loop
asyncpg (async PostgreSQL driver) prevents blocking I/O
Concurrent ingestion of 5 RSS feeds + SEC API + market data
All NLP processing parallelized with asyncio.gather()
Separation of Concerns

Ingestion tier (Celery): fetches raw data
Processing tier (NLP): enriches with NER, sentiment
Computation tier (risk engine): quantitative scoring
Presentation tier (API/WebSocket): exposes results
Caching Strategy

Read cache (Redis) for expensive queries (risk score computations)
Pub/Sub cache for event broadcasting (avoids database polling)
TTL-based invalidation (5-min for scores, 1-min for alerts)
NLP Pipeline Design

Lazy-loaded spaCy model (on-demand, not in startup)
Batch processing of articles to amortize model loading
Async execution in thread pool (spaCy is CPU-bound)
Vector Search

Hybrid retrieval: semantic (Qdrant) + keyword (PostgreSQL)
Sentence transformers for embeddings
Useful for "find similar risk patterns" queries
API Rate Limiting

slowapi middleware with configurable limits
Prevents abuse and API quota exhaustion
Key by remote IP address
