Key Trade-Off Explanations:

1. Async-First Design vs Sync-Everything

Trade: Learning curve + complexity vs throughput + responsiveness
RiskLens choice: Async (ingesting 500+ signals/hour needs concurrency)
Cost: Developers must understand async/await + event loops
Benefit: 10x throughput without adding servers
2. PostgreSQL vs MongoDB

Trade: Schema flexibility vs data consistency
RiskLens choice: PostgreSQL (financial data needs ACID guarantees)
Cost: Must define schema upfront (Alembic migrations)
Benefit: No data corruption; SQL is well-understood
3. JWT vs Sessions

Trade: Server-side control vs stateless scalability
RiskLens choice: JWT (6-month expiry per config)
Cost: Can't invalidate token immediately (except in Redis blacklist — not implemented)
Benefit: Can run multiple backend instances without shared state
4. Fixed Risk Formula vs ML Model

Trade: Interpretability vs predictive accuracy
RiskLens choice: Fixed formula (sentiment + volume + price)
Cost: May miss subtle patterns
Benefit: Analysts can understand "why score is 85"; easy to debug
5. Vector + Keyword Search (Hybrid) vs Vector-Only

Trade: Complexity vs recall
RiskLens choice: Hybrid (semantic + keyword)
Cost: Two queries per search
Benefit: Catches both conceptual matches + exact keyword matches
